name: Multiply operator
content: All programming languages support the basic arithmetic operations of addition, subtraction, multiplication and division of numbers.

examples.name: Example: Multiply two numbers

palette_params.name: num1
palette_params.description: The operands can be a number, or a variable containing a number, or the number returned by a function, or the numeric result of the evaluation of an expression.

palette_params.name: num2
palette_params.description: Same as `num1` but serves as the multiplicand of the expression.

return_value: A number, the result of multiplying two numbers.
tips: - Operator precedence is the same as standard arithmetic - Expressions within a parentheses have the highest precedence, then multiplcation and division, then addition and subtraction.
